@UserManagementAPI_HostAddress = http://localhost:5113
@token = 

### 1. AUTHENTICATION TESTS

### 1a. Generate a test token (Development only)
POST {{UserManagementAPI_HostAddress}}/api/auth/token
Accept: application/json

### 1b. Login with API Key
POST {{UserManagementAPI_HostAddress}}/api/auth/login
X-API-Key: dev-api-key-123
Accept: application/json

### 1c. Verify token validity
GET {{UserManagementAPI_HostAddress}}/api/auth/verify
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

###

### 2. ERROR HANDLING TESTS

### 2a. Test - Throw unhandled exception
GET {{UserManagementAPI_HostAddress}}/api/diagnostic/throw-exception
Accept: application/json

### 2b. Test - Throw null exception
GET {{UserManagementAPI_HostAddress}}/api/diagnostic/throw-null-exception
Accept: application/json

### 2c. Test - Throw unauthorized exception
GET {{UserManagementAPI_HostAddress}}/api/diagnostic/throw-unauthorized
Accept: application/json

### 2d. Test - Health check (should succeed)
GET {{UserManagementAPI_HostAddress}}/api/diagnostic/health
Accept: application/json

###

### 3. AUTHORIZATION TESTS

### 3a. Test - Access protected endpoint WITHOUT token (should fail 401)
GET {{UserManagementAPI_HostAddress}}/api/diagnostic/protected
Accept: application/json

### 3b. Test - Access protected endpoint WITH valid token (should succeed)
GET {{UserManagementAPI_HostAddress}}/api/diagnostic/protected
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### 3c. Test - Access protected endpoint WITH invalid token (should fail 401)
GET {{UserManagementAPI_HostAddress}}/api/diagnostic/protected
Authorization: Bearer invalid-token-xyz
Accept: application/json

###

### 4. USER MANAGEMENT TESTS

### 4a. Get all users (requires auth)
GET {{UserManagementAPI_HostAddress}}/api/users
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### 4b. Create user with valid data (requires auth)
POST {{UserManagementAPI_HostAddress}}/api/users
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Doe",
  "email": "john@example.com"
}

### 4c. Create user with invalid email (validation error 400)
POST {{UserManagementAPI_HostAddress}}/api/users
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Jane Doe",
  "email": "invalid-email"
}

### 4d. Create user without name (validation error 400)
POST {{UserManagementAPI_HostAddress}}/api/users
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "",
  "email": "test@example.com"
}

### 4e. Create user without auth (401 Unauthorized)
POST {{UserManagementAPI_HostAddress}}/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "No Auth User",
  "email": "noauth@example.com"
}

### 4f. Update user (requires auth)
PUT {{UserManagementAPI_HostAddress}}/api/users/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Updated Name",
  "email": "updated@example.com"
}

### 4g. Delete user (requires auth)
DELETE {{UserManagementAPI_HostAddress}}/api/users/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

###
